<div class="about-section"><b>Empowerment. Speaking your truth. Being true to ones self. </b></P><b>This is the message Asila brings. </b></P>Asila is a female fronted hard rock band originally from Johannesburg, South Africa.</P> Formed in 2017, the message of Asila is one of strength and self empowerment and the sound is firmly in the hard rock territory, with influences of blues and soul. </P>We call it ‘Rock’n’Soul’.</P>Since 2018 Asila has been releasing singles while working up to their debut album, Acid Rain. </P>Acid Rain promises to be full of catchy choruses, high energy songs and most importantly, a message that lights a fire in the heart of the listener.</P>With two videos releases, one for Resistance featuring a Tarantino-esque murder mystery and one for Ignite, showing the growth of the band, Asila aims to release another video soon for their upcoming single Hot Blooded Woman.</P>As of 2019, the members of Asila have migrated across the world to in California, USA and Nottingham, UK as well as maintaining roots in South Africa, but the band has been writing, recording and fighting on.</P>  <h3>&nbsp</h3><div class="band-divider">    <hr></hr>  </div> </div><section class="section members" id="members-section">  <div class=wrap>      <div class="wrap row small-up-1 medium-up-2 large-up-2">      <div class="members-item column column-block section-text">Hana Muftic - Vocals	  <p/><p/>	  	  <a href="<?php echo esc_url( home_url( '/' ) ); ?>band/hana" class="member-image column"><img src="<?php bloginfo('template_directory'); ?>/images/hana.jpg"  title="Hana Muftic" class="member-image column" alt="Asila Hana image"/></a> </div>      <div class="members-item column column-block section-text">Richard Globisch - Guitar	  <p/><p/>       <a href="<?php echo esc_url( home_url( '/' ) ); ?>band/rich" class="member-image column"><img src="<?php bloginfo('template_directory'); ?>/images/rich.jpg"  title="Richard Globisch" class="mem